cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about predicting future images given a sequence of present images. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper proposes a model that learns to represent the present state and its transformation to predict future images. This involves the use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) core, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are widely used in computer vision and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of weighted residual connections, which are a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
